run sdgfetch to display system info with your selected logo and preset
sdgfetch-conf lets you pick logos and presets interactively with live previews
add custom logos by placing PNG/JPG images in ~/.config/SDG-FETCH/src/ and running sdgfetch-conf
sdgfetch archlinux shows a themed display using distro-specific colors
run ~/.local/SDG-FETCH/update-files.sh manually to convert new source images to ASCII art
